{
  "text": "At the end of the clamp study (at 240 min), a rapid bolus of intravenous glucose was administered (0.3 g/kg) over 20 s and serial blood samples taken every 2 min for 8 min to measure insulin, C-peptide and glucose. The IVGTT has been used in similar cohorts to assess beta cell function in the past [CITATION_1] .",
